.TH simple_shell 1 "18 October 2023" "1.0" "Simple
Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- Simple shell created in C to interact with a
Linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\-hv] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBsimple_shell\fR is a user-friendly shell program
for interacting with a Linux operating system. 
It reads and executes commands from either a file or the
terminal, providing a command interpreter
with a wide range of features.

.PP
The shell accepts a variety of commands, making it versatile
for both interactive and non-interactive use. 
It can be used for running commands directly or executing
scripts stored in files.

.SH OPTIONS
The following options are supported:

.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help information and exit.

.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display the version of the \fBsimple_shell\fR and exit.

.SH EXAMPLES
.B simple_shell
Runs the \fBsimple_shell\fR in interactive mode.

.TP
.B simple_shell \-v
Displays the version of the \fBsimple_shell\fR.

.TP
.B simple_shell my_script.sh
Executes the commands in the file \fBmy_script.sh\fR.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The \fBsimple_shell\fR returns 0 on success.
Any other return value indicates an error or failure.

.SH AUTHOR
Immanuel Eshun Quansah

